Harris Associates>Strategies & Products


EmailPrint

Bookmark








                            Strategies & Products


Harris Associates offers U.S., international and global investment strategies for individuals and families, pension funds, foundations, endowments and other clients around the world.
StrategiesProductsStrategiesU.S.Equity
Private Client Equity
Customized separate account portfolios that seek long-term capital appreciation. Portfolios generally hold 15-40 securities with market cap focus of $1 billion and above at the time of initial purchase.

U.S Equity
U.S. Equity portfolios hold approximately 40 securities with a market cap focus of $5 billion and above, and typically have a 25% maximum in any industry and 7% maximum position size at the time of initial purchase.

Concentrated Value
Concentrated portfolios hold approximately 20 securities with a market cap focus of $1 billion and above, and typically have a 25% maximum in any industry and 10% maximum position size at the time of initial purchase.

Mid Cap Value
Mid Cap portfolios hold approximately 45 securities with a market cap focus generally between $1 billion and $10 billion, and typically have no more than 25% in any industry and 7% maximum position size at the time of initial purchase.
Balanced
Private Client Balanced
Customized separate account portfolios built according to client-specific guidelines. Equity and fixed-income components work together to seek preservation of capital and long-term growth.

Balanced
Balanced portfolios typically hold 20 equity securities with market cap focus above $1 billion at time of initial purchase, and fixed-income securities of high quality and short to intermediate duration.
Global Equity
Global
Global portfolios generally hold 40 to 50 equity securities with a market cap focus over $5 billion, and typically have no more than 30% in any country (except U.S.), 25% in any industry and 10% maximum position size at the time of initial purchase.

Global All Cap
Global All Cap portfolios generally hold 30 to 60 securities with a market cap focus of $1 billion and above, and typically have no more than 30% in any country (except U.S.), 25% in any industry and 7% maximum position size at the time of initial purchase.

Global Concentrated
Global Concentrated portfolios hold approximately 20 securities with a market cap focus of $5 billion and above, and typically have no more than 30% in any country (except U.S.), 30% in any industry and 15% maximum position size at the time of initial purchase.
International Equity
International
International portfolios generally hold 35 to 65 equity securities with a market cap focus above $5 billion, and typically have no more than 30% in any country, 25% in any industry and 7% maximum position size at the time of initial purchase.

International Small Cap
International Small Cap portfolios generally hold 35 to 70 equity securities with a market cap focus under $5 billion, and typically have no more than 30% in any country, 25% in any industry and 7% maximum position size at the time of initial purchase.

Japan Equity
Japan Equity portfolios hold the securities of 20 to 30 Japanese companies with a market cap focus of $3 billion and above, and typically have no more than 35% in any industry and 10% maximum position size at the time of initial purchase.
ProductsSeparate Accounts
Custom-managed accounts for individuals, families, foundations, endowments, pension plans and mutual funds

Commingled Vehicles
Investments available only to accredited investors as defined by the Securities Act of 1933 or ERISA-qualified retirement plans and certain other government plans

Sub-advisory Services
Customized portfolio management with simplified administration for financial advisors

The Oakmark Funds
A value-oriented mutual fund family offering U.S., balanced, global and international funds






