Bookmark








                            Careers


Discipline is the Harris Associates way. Our long, consistent record of excellence is built on our fundamental belief in value investing, which goes beyond short-term performance, focusing on long-term quality and returns.  In constructing portfolios for our clients, we seek out companies that we believe are trading at significant discounts to their underlying value. We view every stock purchase as if we were buying a piece of a business, not just a stock certificate. We look for managers who seek to maximize the long-term value of the business for its owners by running efficient operations, concentrating on cash flow and allocating capital wisely. Our belief in our process helps us to stand firm in our philosophy through the natural ebbs and flows of the markets, striving to exceed our clients’ high expectations. 
 
At our core, we believe in good investments. This rings especially true for our most important assets — our employees. Work-life balance is important in our culture, with world-class benefits and a friendly atmosphere. As a firm of about 200 people, we’re proud to offer opportunities for those who want to create their own path; to prove themselves and be recognized for hard work; to thrive in a team environment. Harris is a place where everyone is experienced in their field, yet is eager to learn more.

OpportunitiesBenefits at HarrisHow to ApplyOpportunitiesEvery Harris employee has the opportunity to make a difference, grow his or her career and collaborate with peers who are passionate about their work. We have a relentless commitment to attracting, developing and retaining our greatest assets — our employees. 
 
Click here to check out our currently available opportunities.
Benefits at HarrisOur dedication to providing a robust benefits package was instituted based on the belief that employees should not worry about their family’s access to healthcare. Today, Harris employees enjoy a comprehensive benefits package which they are eligible to enroll in on their first day of employment. A summary is below:
 
Healthcare Benefits:
 - Medical and Rx 
 - Dental Insurance
 - Vision Insurance
 - Health Reimbursement Account (HRA)
 - Flexible Spending Accounts (FSA)
 - Life Insurance & Accidental Death and Dismemberment (AD&D) Insurance
 - Short-Term Disability Insurance
 - Long-Term Disability Insurance
 - Long-Term Care Insurance
Financial Benefits:
 - Profit Sharing
 - 401(k)
 - Tuition Loan Program
Family Benefits:
 - Back-Up Childcare
 - Paid Parental Leave
 - Adoption Assistance
Additional Perks:
 - Paid Holidays & Generous Paid Time Off
 - Wellness Benefits
 - Catered Lunch Every Day
 - Commuter Transit Benefit
 - Employee Assistance Program (EAP)
How to ApplyTo view our currently available opportunities, please click here.
If you’re not quite ready to apply, or don’t see an open position that fits your skills and interests, join our talent community through the Discover Your Potential section. Discover Your Potential allows you to personalize your job search by providing your ideal job title, education, licenses and certifications. Once complete, you’ll receive notifications when opportunities open up that could be a match for your background and career goals.
 
If you need assistance with this process, please contact Human Resources at (312) 646-3240.
 
Privacy Statement
The information you send to us is used for employment purposes only. What you send is kept confidential — we will not give your personal information to outside parties without your consent.
 
Equal Employment Opportunity Policy Statement
Harris Associates L.P. (“Harris Associates” or the “Firm”) pursues a policy of equal opportunity in all areas of employment including recruitment, hiring, training, compensation, benefits, advancement and treatment on the job. This means that the Firm prohibits discrimination against employees and applicants on the basis of race, color, religion, gender, sexual orientation, pregnancy, gender identity, national origin, age, disability, genetic information, veteran status, military status and marital status or any other characteristic protected by applicable law.






